<br>
I don't know Cukak very well, only met him a couple times but I do know that he was in EJ since the servers came up because I periodically popped in to check.<br>
<br>
I further know Ferdian was there waiting for him as well every time I checked.<br>
<br>
I didn't know they were together, and had no communication with them about Sev, but I know they were both there for a LOOONG time, at no time did I check EJ and they were not there.<br>
<br>
I was in SF when I got asked if I wanted to burn Sev, and I said yes. I know from the time I zoned in there was not a single /ooc /shout or /auc on this or any other subject.<br>
<br>
The necro (Cukak) died pulling (as I thought he would but god damn he's brave) and then Mont pulled. At this point there was what appeared to be a 'fib' in /ooc saying leave Sev alone and they had been claiming Sev. Sev was pulled at this point so it was moot anyway, but I asked the others who had been there before and they said there had been no /ooc on the subject. These are people I know and don't think they would lie. And I know Ferd and Cukak had been there for <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> many</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> hours.<br>
<br>
I can assure you if I zoned in and saw that in /ooc I would have memmed a gate and left.<br>
<br>
It's an unfortunate situation, and I am sympathetic but I do not think there is anything nefarious about it. All I can say is camp the mob, do like you said and announce the fact periodically and the problem should not recur.<br>
<br>
If in the furture you need fast help to kill something I will be happy to assist. Sev will pop again in a few days and I'll be glad to help your Warrior get his scale.<br>
<br>
And in general if you want something like a green scale another thing to do is send burners tells asking for help if you think you may need it. This clearly establishes that you got to the mob first. MOST burners will treat this as priveleged information, and will not spread it around if they can't go. I won't name names but you probably have a good idea who to trust and who not to.<br>
<br>
