 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/utiqua.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tiqua</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Froglok Guk Knight</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(7/25/02 1:36:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=417.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Something I hoped never to see</span><hr size=1> The druid was also in EJ since servers came back up.  Even before that.  And as soon as Sev pops the druid did say in ooc several times that we were going to try and kill Sev.  The druid logged off to his warrior after several VoR people arrived in the zone.  I can't tell you exactly how many people were in the zone when you killed Sev b/c I was on my wizard porting a few more in.  I do know that I zoned in after Sev dropped and before Montague zoned back into EJ that there were at least 14 VoR (15 if you count the LD) and 4 nonVoR there.  Also if you add my shaman that was camped out so I could port stragglers that'll give you the 20.<br>
